                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      New Hero Honda facility
                            
	Bangalore, March 28 (PTI): The Karnataka government is allotting 500 acres near Dharwad to Hero Honda to set up a Rs 2,000-crore two-wheeler manufacturing plant with an annual capacity of 1 lakh units, the states large and medium industries minister Murugesh R. Nirani said.         
	Hero Honda is coming. We are going to give them 500 acres near Hubli airport near Dharwad. They need 1,000 skilled workers, Nirani said.         
	He said he would hold a second round of discussion with South Korean steel major Posco in Seoul in the first week of April regarding the companys plans to set up a steel plant with an annual capacity of six million tonnes at an investment of Rs 32,000 crore in the state.                                                                                                                                                    
